Reference-contexts: Moreover, strategic decisions have to be taken by the SEAC which may lead to the application of different schema evolution techniques (cf. <ref> [Lem94b] </ref>). Basic schema evolution commands are essentially the commands described in the SEA tool specification ([Lem94a]), e.g., the addition of an attribute to a class, which are supported by the CSME for direct execution on the Chimera Interpreter.
