Reference-contexts: Looking for an elegant solution for the problem of schema management, we decided to use the Chimera DBMS itself for this task. As we have already pointed out in <ref> [Lem95] </ref>, this requires the definition of a meta schema for the representation of Chimera schemas, but immediately offers all the means the Chimera DBMS provides for, e.g., browsing, querying, integrity checking, and trigger activation.
